linux basic commands
------------------------------
1. hostname [to chekc the hostname of the system]
2. who am i [to check user]
3. hostnamectl [show sys name]
4. hostnamectl set-hostname name [to change the hostname of sys]
5.  pwd [present working directory]
6. cd [change directory]
[ a.. cd aur folder name
 b. cd /root [full address/ absolute path]
7. cat > file1 [to create file and edit it]
save it by ctr+d
8. cat file1 [to read the file]
9. touch f1 f2 f3  [ to create multiple files]
10. echo "pin is 123" > account [to add data into the file]
11. vi filename [to create a file or read the file in edit mode]
[to save press esc and :wq, without save :q]
12. rm filename [to remove file]
13. rm -rf foldername [to remove folder]
14. mv sourcefilename destinationfilename [to change the name of the file]
15. cat >> file1 [to add content in the created file ]
16. cat file1 file2 > mainfile [to merge two files]

